                <h2 class="centered-text">What is a One Person Company (OPC)?</h2>
                <div class="content-row">
                    <div class="content-text">
                        <h3>Combining simplicity with corporate benefits.</h3>
                        <p>A **One Person Company (OPC)** is a hybrid business entity introduced in India by the Companies Act, 2013, to support entrepreneurs who wish to start a venture alone, without the complexities of a traditional Private Limited Company, yet with the benefits of a corporate structure.</p>
                        <p>It allows a single person to form a company with limited liability, meaning the personal assets of the sole owner are protected from the liabilities of the business. An OPC offers perpetual succession and ease of raising funds, making it an attractive option for individual entrepreneurs. This innovative structure addresses the unique needs of sole proprietors seeking a formal corporate identity.</p>
                    </div>
