        <section class="content-section key-advantages fade-in-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="centered-text">Key Benefits of OPC Registration</h2>
                <p class="centered-text">Experience the advantages of a corporate structure tailored for individual entrepreneurs.</p>
                <div class="benefits-grid">
                    <div class="benefit-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i>
                        <h3>Limited Liability Protection</h3>
                        <p>The liability of the single member is limited to the extent of capital contributed. Personal assets are fully protected against business liabilities, ensuring peace of mind.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="benefit-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-project-diagram"></i>
                        <h3>Separate Legal Entity</h3>
                        <p>An OPC is distinct from its owner. It can own property, enter contracts, and sue or be sued in its own name, offering significant operational flexibility.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="benefit-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-infinity"></i>
                        <h3>Perpetual Succession</h3>
                        <p>Unlike a sole proprietorship, an OPC's existence is independent of its owner. A nominee ensures continuity, making it a stable and long-term business vehicle.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="benefit-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-hand-holding-usd"></i>
                        <h3>Greater Credibility & Funding</h3>
                        <p>Corporate status enhances credibility among suppliers, customers, and lenders, making it easier to access credit and loans compared to informal setups.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="benefit-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                        <h3>Complete Control</h3>
                        <p>The single owner retains absolute control over all business decisions, providing unmatched autonomy without interference from other shareholders or directors.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="benefit-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-tasks"></i>
                        <h3>Less Compliance Burden</h3>
                        <p>Compared to a Private Limited Company, an OPC faces fewer mandatory compliance requirements, simplifying management and reducing administrative overheads.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="benefit-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-rupee-sign"></i>
                        <h3>No Minimum Capital</h3>
                        <p>As per the Companies (Amendment) Act, 2015, there is no minimum paid-up capital requirement for forming an OPC, making it accessible for entrepreneurs with varying capital bases.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="benefit-item">
                        <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                        <h3>Brand Value & Tax Benefits</h3>
                        <p>Establishing an OPC enhances your business's brand value. It is also taxed as a private company, potentially offering certain tax benefits depending on income levels.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
