        <section class="content-section key-advantages fade-in-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="centered-text">Eligibility and Restrictions for an OPC</h2>
                <div class="eligibility-container">
                    <div class="eligibility-item">
                        <h3>Who Can Form an OPC?</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Only a natural person who is an **Indian Citizen and resident in India** is eligible.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> "Resident in India" means a person who has stayed in India for a period of **not less than 120 days** during the immediately preceding financial year.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> A person can **only incorporate one OPC**.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> The nominee for the OPC must also be an Indian Citizen and resident in India.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="eligibility-item">
                        <h3>Who Cannot Form an OPC?</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> An **NRI (Non-Resident Indian)** is not eligible to incorporate an OPC.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> A **minor** shall not be eligible to become a member or nominee of an OPC.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> An OPC cannot carry out **non-banking financial investment activities**, including investment in securities of any body corporate.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> An OPC **cannot be converted into a Section 8 Company** (Non-profit organization).</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> An OPC cannot convert into any other form of company unless **two years have expired from the date of incorporation**, except in case of threshold limits (paid-up capital exceeds 50 Lakhs or average annual turnover exceeds 2 Crore).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="process fade-in-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="centered-text">Our Streamlined OPC Registration Process</h2>
                <p class="centered-text" style="color: var(--text-light);">Making your OPC incorporation smooth and efficient, step-by-step.</p>
                <div class="process-steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-id-card"></i></div>
                        <h3>1. DSC & DIN Application</h3>
                        <p>Initiate the process by obtaining Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) and Director Identification Number (DIN) for the proposed Director and their Nominee.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i></div>
                        <h3>2. Name Reservation</h3>
                        <p>Apply for reservation of your unique company name with the Ministry of Corporate Affairs (MCA) using the RUN (Reserve Unique Name) service.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i></div>
                        <h3>3. MOA & AOA Drafting</h3>
                        <p>Draft the Memorandum of Association (MOA) and Articles of Association (AOA), which define the company's objectives and internal regulations.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-upload"></i></div>
                        <h3>4. Document Filing with MCA</h3>
                        <p>Submit the integrated SPICe+ Form (Part A for name reservation, Part B for incorporation) along with e-MOA, e-AOA, and other necessary declarations to the MCA.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-certificate"></i></div>
                        <h3>5. Certificate of Incorporation</h3>
                        <p>Upon successful verification and approval of all documents, the Registrar of Companies issues the Certificate of Incorporation for your OPC.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-university"></i></div>
                        <h3>6. PAN & TAN Allotment</h3>
                        <p>With the Certificate of Incorporation, the Permanent Account Number (PAN) and Tax Deduction and Collection Account Number (TAN) for your OPC are automatically generated and allotted.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

